"```sql\nSELECT \n  (COUNT(DISTINCT fd.id) * 100.0 / (SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT id) FROM cards)) AS percentage\nFROM \n  foreign_data fd\nWHERE \n  fd.language = 'Chinese Simplified';\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the percentage of cards available in Chinese Simplified by counting the distinct IDs in the `foreign_data` table where the language is 'Chinese Simplified' and dividing it by the total number of distinct card IDs in the `cards` table."